@startuml developer-onboarding
title Developer Onboarding — Register + Run Middleware (Arc Testnet)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #FFF3E0
skinparam participantBorderColor #FF9800

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "Circle Faucet\n(faucet.circle.com)" as Faucet
participant "register CLI\n(scripts/register.ts)" as CLI
participant "PaymentSplitter\nContract (Arc Testnet)" as Splitter
participant "Developer Service\n(withPaywall middleware)" as Service

== Step 1: Get test USDC ==
Dev -> Faucet : Request 1 USDC on Arc Testnet
Faucet -> Dev : USDC arrives at developer wallet\n(also pays Arc gas — USDC is native gas token)

== Step 2: Register wallet ==
Dev -> CLI : npx universal-paywall register \\\n  --wallet 0xDev... \\\n  --network arc-testnet
note over CLI : REGISTER_KEY env var holds\nthe developer's private key
CLI -> Splitter : register(0xDev...)
Splitter -> Splitter : developers[0xDev].registered = true\nemit DeveloperRegistered(0xDev)
Splitter --> CLI : tx hash
CLI -> Dev : ✅ Registered (link to arcscan)

== Step 3: Install + configure middleware ==
Dev -> Service : npm install @universal-paywall/middleware

Dev -> Service : Server code:\n\nimport { withPaywall } from\n  '@universal-paywall/middleware';\n\nconst server = http.createServer(\n  withPaywall(myHandler, {\n    price: '0.01',\n    developerId: '0xDev...',\n    network: 'arc-testnet',\n    facilitator: {\n      mode: 'inline',\n      relayerKey: process.env.PAYWALL_RELAYER_KEY\n    }\n  })\n);

note over Service
  Contract address baked into the
  middleware package per NETWORKS map.
  Relayer key funds Arc gas — needs USDC.
  Can be the developer's own key for
  open-source self-hosting (relayer == developer).
end note

== Step 4: Balance check & withdrawal ==

Dev -> Splitter : getBalance(0xDev)
Splitter -> Dev : balance (micro-USDC)

Dev -> Splitter : withdraw(amount) \\\n  (signed from 0xDev)
Splitter -> Splitter : require msg.sender == 0xDev\nrequire balance >= amount\nbalance -= amount
Splitter -> Dev : USDC transfer → 0xDev

@enduml
